  "prompt": "Indian Air Force: Can I stay with my family during the service after long hours of duty (daily) if not on leave?",
  "response": "Whether you can stay with your family during your service in the Indian Air Force depends on your specific posting and role. Generally, military personnel may have the opportunity to live with their families if they are posted to a non-combat area where family accommodation is available. Many air force bases provide family housing facilities, which allow personnel to stay with their families when not on duty or during off-hours.\n\nHowever, operational requirements, postings to combat zones, or remote locations might not have such provisions, requiring personnel to stay in single accommodations or barracks separate from their families. In these cases, family visits and leaves are typically planned according to the service requirements and personal leave entitlements.\n\nIt's best to check with Indian Air Force administration or personnel division for specific regulations and possibilities related to your situation.",
